# Example Environment Variables

This file documents the environment variables used by this project.
Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your local values.

```bash
# ============================================================================
# Database Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Database user password (example only - change for local development)
DATABASE_PASSWORD=

# Database username (if applicable)
DATABASE_USER=

# ============================================================================
# API Configuration
# ============================================================================

# API keys or access tokens
API_KEY=

# OAuth or bearer tokens
AUTH_TOKEN=

# ============================================================================
# Security & SSL
# ============================================================================

# SSL/TLS keystore password (if using HTTPS)
SSL_KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=

# ============================================================================
# Build & Testing
# ============================================================================

# NVD API key for dependency vulnerability scanning (optional)
NVD_APIKEY_SEDR=

# GitHub token for semantic-release and pre-push hook validation
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ============================================================================
# Application Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Application-specific variables
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_LOG_LEVEL=INFO
